The Telegraph - Calcutta : International

 Glacier wave

 Oslo, Aug. 9 (Reuters): A chunk of an Arctic glacier broke into the sea and triggered a huge wave that injured 18 people on a sightseeing boat, Norwegian officials said today. Almost all were British tourists

 Four people were seriously hurt in the accident by Hornbreen glacier on the Norwegian archipelago of Svalbard and were flown south to a hospital in Tromsoe on the mainland.




